<h2 id="implementation-reality">🛠️ Implementation Reality</h2>

Software migrations are painful. Anyone who tells you otherwise hasn't done one at scale. Here's what to expect with a Glofox implementation:

**Week 1:** Account setup, payment processor connection, basic configuration. Your Glofox rep handles most of this, but you'll need to provide business details, branding assets, and banking information.

**Week 2:** Data migration. Member records, billing info, and historical data transfer. Glofox's migration team handles the technical work, but you'll need to clean your export data and verify post-migration accuracy.

**Week 3:** Staff training and parallel operation. Run both systems simultaneously for at least a week. Train staff on the new interface, test booking flows, and work out the inevitable workflow adjustments.

**Week 4:** Go live and monitoring. Cut over fully, closely monitor billing cycles, and have all-hands-on-deck for member questions.

<div class="callout-blue">
<strong>Tip:</strong> Schedule your migration to start after your billing cycle runs in your old system. This minimizes the complexity of partial-month prorations during transition.
</div>

